      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a complex ideology with both positive and negative facets. When it fosters a strong sense of shared identity and civic duty, it can contribute to social cohesion and a stable political unit. However, nationalism becomes dangerous when it morphs into chauvinism, leading to xenophobia, aggressive nationalism, and the marginalization of minority groups. Ultimately, its impact depends heavily on whether it emphasizes inclusive shared values or exclusive group superiority.",
