      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're touching on the inherent tension between national self-interest and global cooperation, which is a key political dilemma. While national self-determination necessitates prioritizing internal needs, this doesn't automatically mandate antagonism toward others; international institutions allow for sovereign nations to pursue interests while maintaining global obligations. The historical tendency toward aggression often stems from *extreme* forms of nationalism, those that reject all external relationships rather than merely asserting internal identity.",
      "source": "target",
